Package rest

The Triplifier's server-side REST service implementation.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
Attribute Represents a RDF literal property created from a database table.
Connection Represents a database connection, can be used to generate a JDBC URL, make a new D2RQ Database or generate a D2RQ Mapping entry.
ContextListener Registers/unregisters JDBC drivers listed in DBsystem when context is initialized/destroyed.
Dataseturi Represents a DataSet and places the DataSet at the top level of the graph.
DBtable Represents a table in a database schema.
Entity Represents a RDF resource created from a database table.
Join Represents a relational join between two database tables.
Mapping Performs two major tasks: - constructor inspects SQL database and generates schema, - printD2RQ translates connection, entities and relations into D2RQ Mapping Language.
RDFclass Represents RDF class in a vocabulary, can have sub-classes.
RDFproperty Represents RDF property in a vocabulary, can have sub-properties, domain and range.
RDFreader Reads RDF file, extracts Vocabulary containing classes and properties to use in interface.
Relation Represents a relation between the subject and object Entities.
Rest Provides RESTful web services using Jersey JAX-RS implementation.
Vocabulary Represents a vocabulary, where classes can be used to describe Entity.rdfClass and properties can be used to describe Attribute.rdfProperty.
VocabularyItem Represents an item in a vocabulary with name and URI only.
WadlResources Describes the REST service in a human readable manner
 

Enum Summary
DBsystem Enumerates supported database systems with their JDBC drivers.
 

Package rest Description

The Triplifier's server-side REST service implementation.
